As a recovering coffee addict (half lie), I require at least 7 hot drinks to get me through the day. 

I've always loved tea it that very British way, soaking a teabag for a few minutes before removing and adding milk. Most teabags contain either pure Assam or a blend of Assam, Ceylon and Kenya (also called English Breakfast blend).

These teas are named after the regions from which they originated. Assam; in north eastern India, Ceylon; in Sri Lanka and Kenya; in, well, Kenya.

But the variety of teas stretch far beyond these

Whilst in the US I learned to love loose leaf tea.

